2 Aug 2018 16:59:28 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Memberlite\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/?p=158592\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1443:\"This update prepares Memberlite further for submission to the WordPress.org theme repository. One requirement for this is that some functionality needed to be moved into plugins. Functionality around banners, sidebars, and widgets have been moved into the Memberlite Elements plugin. After upgrading to Memberlite 4.0, you will need to install the new Memberlite Elements plugin. Use the steps below to upgrade Memberlite and install the new required plugin. As soon as the theme is accepted into the WordPress.org theme repository, we will push out a minor update to tell the theme to update through WordPress.org going forward. To find out more about Memberlite 4.0, you can now browse the demo site of the entire Memberlite Theme or view full theme documentation at the Memberlite Theme Support Site. &#160; Adhering to WordPress theme standards and best practices. In preparation for the theme&#8217;s submission to the WordPress.org Themes Repository we&#8217;ve updated the code to fully adhere to WordPress&#8217; standards and guidelines as outlined in the Theme Check plugin. We also purchased a theme review from Justin Tadlock atThemeReview.co, which prompted additional updates to harden up our code base and make it more reliable and secure for all users. In Memberlite v3.0 all <a href=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/memberlite-4-0-bug-fixes-improvements-memberlite-elements-and-upgrade-migration-steps/\">(more...)</a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Jason Coleman\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7127:\"<div class=\"lead\"><p><div class=\"row \"><div class=\"medium-8  columns\">\n<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce a new phase in the Memberlite theme lifecycle plus the release of the <a href=\"https://memberlitetheme.com/memberlite-elements/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Memberlite Elements plugin</a>.</p>\n<p></p></div><div class=\"medium-4  columns\"><img data-attachment-id=\"158600\" data-permalink=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/memberlite-4-0-bug-fixes-improvements-memberlite-elements-and-upgrade-migration-steps/memberlite_v4/\" data-orig-file=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4.png\" data-orig-size=\"512,512\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Memberlite v4.0\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4-300x300.png\" data-large-file=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4.png\" src=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4.png\" alt=\"Memberlite v4.0\" width=\"512\" height=\"512\" class=\"size-full wp-image-158600\" srcset=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4.png 512w, https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4-150x150.png 150w, https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4-300x300.png 300w, https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Memberlite_v4-80x80.png 80w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></div>\n</div></div><hr /></p>\n<p>This update prepares Memberlite further for submission to the WordPress.org theme repository. One requirement for this is that some functionality needed to be moved into plugins. Functionality around banners, sidebars, and widgets have been moved into the Memberlite Elements plugin. <strong>After upgrading to Memberlite 4.0, you will need to install the new Memberlite Elements plugin.</strong> <a href=\"#already\">Use the steps below</a> to upgrade Memberlite and install the new required plugin.</p>\n<p>As soon as the theme is accepted into the WordPress.org theme repository, we will push out a minor update to tell the theme to update through WordPress.org going forward.</p>\n<p>To find out more about Memberlite 4.0, you can now browse the <a href=\"https://demo.memberlitetheme.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">demo site of the entire Memberlite Theme</a> or view full theme documentation <a href=\"https://memberlitetheme.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">at the Memberlite Theme Support Site</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"row \"><div class=\"medium-6  columns\"><a class=\"btn btn_action btn_block\" href=\"https://demo.memberlitetheme.com\" target=\"_blank\">Memberlite Demo Site</a></div>\n<div class=\"medium-6  columns\"><a class=\"btn btn_secondary btn_block\" href=\"https://memberlitetheme.com\" target=\"_blank\">Memberlite Website</a></div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Adhering to WordPress theme standards and best practices.</h2>\n<p>In preparation for the theme&#8217;s submission to the WordPress.org Themes Repository we&#8217;ve updated the code to fully adhere to WordPress&#8217; standards and guidelines as outlined in the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/theme-check/\">Theme Check plugin</a>. We also purchased a theme review from Justin Tadlock at<a href=\"http://themereview.co/\">ThemeReview.co</a>, which prompted additional updates to harden up our code base and make it more reliable and secure for all users.</p>\n<p>In Memberlite v3.0 all shortocdes were extracted to a separate plugin: Memberlite Shortcodes. For Memberlite v4.0, some other functionality around banners, sidebars, and widgets have now been moved to a new plugin Memberlite Elements.</p>\n<div class=\"row \"><div class=\"medium-6  columns\">\n<a class=\"btn btn_secondary btn_block\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/memberlite-elements/\" target=\"_self\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\"></i>Memberlite Elements Plugin</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"medium-6  columns\">\n<a class=\"btn btn_secondary btn_block\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/memberlite-shortcodes/\" target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-download\"></i>Memberlite Shortcodes Plugin</a></div>\n</div>\n<hr />\n<h2>Style Updates</h2>\n<p>Memberlite v4.0 has a few relatively minor, but impactful, style updates.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The default font size has been increased for improved readability. This should look fine on most sites, but you may need to tweak some content and styles on your site to get things to fit with the new sizing.</li>\n<li>We are now including some web safe fonts (Arial, Helvetica, Times, etc.) in addition to the Google Fonts previously available.</li>\n<li>Font Awesome has been updated to version 5.2, offering new icons and icon styles (regular, solid and brand).</li>\n<li>Buttons have been given a hover effect to grab the attention of your users.</li>\n<li>A new [memberlite_accordion] shortcode has been added to Memberlite Shortcodes.</li>\n<li>Additional theme Hooks and Filters have been added to support individual site customization as well as child theme development.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"already\">Already using the Memberlite Theme?</h2>\n<p>Below are the step-by-step directions for upgrading to the new version and installing the companion Memberlite Shortcodes plugin. <strong>Before beginning this process we recommend taking a backup of your WordPress site.</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Back up your site files and database <a href=\"https://www.paidmembershipspro.com/set-up-a-data-backup-process-for-your-wordpress-membership-site/\">[instructions]</a></li>\n<li>Install and activate the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/memberlite-elements/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Memberlite Elements</a> plugin.</li>\n<li>Upgrade your theme via the WordPress Updates admin page, or download the theme and upload it to your <code>/wp-content/themes/</code> folder.</li>\n<li>If you haven&#8217;t already, consider installing the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/memberlite-shortcodes/\">Memberlite Shortcodes</a> plugin.</li>\n<li>If you are using a caching plugin, delete and rebuild your cache.</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"pmpro_message pmpro_alert\">PMPro Plus members can get support for this upgrade process via the Members Forum. Just open a topic and we will schedule a time to perform your upgrade.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Learn more about Memberlite 4.0 at the links below.</h2>\n<div class=\"row \"><div class=\"medium-6  columns\"><a class=\"btn btn_action btn_block\" href=\"https://demo.memberlitetheme.com\" target=\"_blank\">Memberlite Demo Site</a></div>\n<div class=\"medium-6  columns\"><a class=\"btn btn_secondary btn_block\" href=\"https://memberlitetheme.com\" target=\"_blank\">Memberlite Website</a></div>\n</div>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";